{
  "texts": [
    "The experimental analysis of KeyBLD [74] indicates that it outperforms the relevant state-of-the-art approaches and is faster than them.",
    "Utilizing BERT for Integrating Semantic InformationThe bidirectional property of BERT-based models enables the learning of the context (i.e., semantic information) of unlabeled texts from both the left and the right sides, and lays the foundation for obtaining contextualized embeddings.We first briefly discuss the use of BERT-based models for aggregating long documents in Section 3.3.1 and then present ranking strategies in Section 3.3.2.",
    "We then cover techniques of weak supervision that leverage BERT-like models in Section 3.3.3.",
    "Finally, we provide an extended comparison and analyses based on experiments in Section 3.3.4.",
    "Aggregation Methods for Long Documents.A number of state-of-the-art approaches [74,132,144,147] can be considered to be aggregation techniques that combine shorter segments of texts to handle long documents.Aggregation-guided BERT models for IR can be divided into three groups, sentence-level score aggregation, passage-level score aggregation, and passage-level representation aggregation, as shown in Table 1."
  ]
